<item>
            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-3253] client should not send requests with cxid=-4, -2, or -1</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-3253</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Once the cxid value increments to -4, the client will interpret the response as an auth packet rather than as a response to a request and will transparently drop the response and the request will hang.&#160; Similarly, -2 will be seen as a ping and will be dropped hanging the request.&#160; -1 shows up as a WatcherEvent and results in the error below.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
